sentences: Irving Solomon "Irv" Teibel (October 9, 1938 – October 28, 2010) was an American field recordist, graphic designer, and photographer.
He also took night classes in electronic music at The New School during this time and was a founding resident of the famous Westbeth Artists Community.

In 1973, to demonstrate how magnetic tape could be manipulated, Teibel edited Richard Nixon’s August 15th speech to reveal that the president, in fact, had “prior knowledge” of the Watergate break-in.
In the subsequent years, Teibel performed as an expert witness for magnetic tape technology.
